1
00:00:14,567 --> 00:00:17,067
Days pass by without
hearing anything about

2
00:00:17,133 --> 00:00:18,567
the investigation.

3
00:00:18,633 --> 00:00:22,700
I feel like dying
from fear and worry.

4
00:00:22,767 --> 00:00:23,667
Is that her?

5
00:00:23,733 --> 00:00:24,833
Yes, that's her.

6
00:00:24,900 --> 00:00:28,267
Didn't I tell you to stop
talking to your brother?

7
00:00:28,333 --> 00:00:30,000
He brings nothing
but trouble.

8
00:00:30,067 --> 00:00:32,133
At least he can do the
thing you're not able to do.

9
00:00:32,200 --> 00:00:34,967
I just want to
slit your throat!

10
00:00:37,867 --> 00:00:39,500
Good job, guys.

11
00:00:39,567 --> 00:00:41,467
Keep on working together.

12
00:00:41,533 --> 00:00:43,800
It's good that you two
are getting along...

13
00:00:44,867 --> 00:00:47,433
especially in
a circumstance like this.

14
00:00:47,500 --> 00:00:49,200
You need to work together.

15
00:00:49,267 --> 00:00:52,333
If you're trying to kill
me, then I'm not afraid!

16
00:00:52,400 --> 00:00:54,433
Because I'm already dead!

17
00:00:54,500 --> 00:00:57,467
You took my right to take
care of my daughter!

18
00:00:57,533 --> 00:01:03,467
You took even the tiny
hope of being with her!

19
00:01:03,533 --> 00:01:06,767
Why didn't you pick an inmate
who could get things done?

20
00:01:06,833 --> 00:01:09,533
Someone who could
do what I want!

21
00:01:09,633 --> 00:01:11,100
Rina, we can try again.

22
00:01:11,167 --> 00:01:12,800
I'll find someone
else to do it.

23
00:01:12,867 --> 00:01:13,967
What for?

24
00:01:14,033 --> 00:01:15,233
It's too late!

25
00:01:15,300 --> 00:01:17,567
They're going to release
that woman out of prison!

26
00:01:17,633 --> 00:01:18,800
Bamboo.

27
00:01:19,933 --> 00:01:21,067
What is it for?

28
00:01:21,133 --> 00:01:23,533
We can collect
rainwater in this.

29
00:01:23,600 --> 00:01:24,433
Coach!

30
00:01:24,500 --> 00:01:27,133
We now have a
supply of water!

31
00:01:27,200 --> 00:01:28,267
Coach, wake up!

32
00:01:28,333 --> 00:01:29,967
- Coach!
- Coach!

33
00:01:30,033 --> 00:01:33,133
We might die out here,
too, like my coach.

34
00:01:33,200 --> 00:01:34,833
I can't let that happen.

35
00:01:34,900 --> 00:01:37,767
Don't you see what's
going on, Red?

36
00:01:37,833 --> 00:01:40,133
It's hopeless!

37
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:44,067
We might have a slight
chance of getting out of here.

38
00:01:44,167 --> 00:01:45,467
But I'm not giving up,
even if it's a long shot.

39
00:01:45,533 --> 00:01:47,233
I will find a way
to get out of here.

40
00:01:47,300 --> 00:01:50,633
Hopelessness is our enemy.

41
00:01:50,700 --> 00:01:53,133
I promise that we
will make it home.

42
00:01:53,200 --> 00:01:55,700
We can celebrate together.

43
00:02:00,400 --> 00:02:01,800
But how?

44
00:02:04,367 --> 00:02:06,267
I don't know how.

45
00:02:09,267 --> 00:02:10,233
We'll think of a way.

46
00:02:14,367 --> 00:02:16,500
Right now, let's say
goodbye to coach first.

47
00:02:59,567 --> 00:03:00,733
Coach,

48
00:03:00,800 --> 00:03:03,300
I'm going to keep
your whistle for now.

49
00:03:04,733 --> 00:03:06,867
Don't worry.

50
00:03:06,933 --> 00:03:10,133
I'll give this back to your
daughter when we get to Manila.

51
00:03:12,600 --> 00:03:16,500
I will tell her how kind
you've been to me...

52
00:03:18,667 --> 00:03:22,700
how you helped us out
and gave us courage

53
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:24,667
while stranded here
on this island.

54
00:03:27,100 --> 00:03:32,933
Even though you
were feeling weak.

55
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:35,133
I'll let her know...

56
00:03:38,667 --> 00:03:47,300
how good her mother is.

57
00:03:59,267 --> 00:04:00,433
Coach...

58
00:04:03,433 --> 00:04:08,267
We will remember
everything you taught us

59
00:04:08,333 --> 00:04:11,533
until we get back to Manila.

60
00:04:13,233 --> 00:04:16,000
I hope you can ask God...

61
00:04:17,967 --> 00:04:20,133
to help us.

62
00:04:23,267 --> 00:04:27,233
We want to go home
to our family.

63
00:04:31,667 --> 00:04:33,200
I pray...

64
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:39,733
that God will save us.

65
00:05:00,600 --> 00:05:02,167
Why is this happening?

66
00:05:02,267 --> 00:05:03,433
Several days have passed,

67
00:05:03,500 --> 00:05:06,533
but they still couldn't locate
where the plane crashed.

68
00:05:07,733 --> 00:05:11,033
Are they doing something
to find my daughter?

69
00:05:11,100 --> 00:05:14,067
Are they doing their job?

70
00:05:14,133 --> 00:05:16,633
Amanda, we were not the
only ones who were there.

71
00:05:16,700 --> 00:05:18,767
All the passengers'
families were there too.

72
00:05:18,833 --> 00:05:22,267
They said the same thing.

73
00:05:22,333 --> 00:05:26,200
They still don't have any
information about the plane.

74
00:05:26,267 --> 00:05:27,800
What do we do now?

75
00:05:27,867 --> 00:05:29,867
Are we just going to wait?

76
00:05:29,933 --> 00:05:32,500
Only God can help us now.

77
00:05:32,567 --> 00:05:36,900
I want to see my daughter.

78
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:38,767
Amanda!

79
00:05:38,833 --> 00:05:40,800
Amanda, are you okay?

80
00:05:40,867 --> 00:05:41,967
Amanda!

81
00:05:47,433 --> 00:05:48,467
Are you okay?

82
00:05:50,367 --> 00:05:53,067
Victor, I can't
take this anymore.

83
00:05:53,133 --> 00:05:55,733
Why can't we
just go to Davao?

84
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:58,767
Let's lead the search
and rescue operation.

85
00:05:58,833 --> 00:06:00,700
Let them do their job, Rina.

86
00:06:00,767 --> 00:06:02,367
They know what they're doing.

87
00:06:02,433 --> 00:06:05,967
If they know what they're
doing, then where is my son?

88
00:06:06,033 --> 00:06:08,067
Can you calm down?

89
00:06:08,167 --> 00:06:10,767
Your rants are not
helping the situation.

90
00:06:10,833 --> 00:06:14,067
Let's get you
something to drink.

91
00:06:14,133 --> 00:06:15,867
No need.

92
00:06:15,933 --> 00:06:18,167
Maybe I'm just stressed out.

93
00:06:19,367 --> 00:06:20,533
I'm okay.

94
00:06:20,600 --> 00:06:23,267
- Are you sure?
- Yes, I'm okay.

95
00:06:23,333 --> 00:06:25,367
I just want our son back.

96
00:06:25,433 --> 00:06:27,633
I know.

97
00:06:27,700 --> 00:06:29,000
Let's go home.

98
00:06:30,667 --> 00:06:31,500
Wait.

99
00:06:33,467 --> 00:06:35,233
That's Amanda!

100
00:06:35,300 --> 00:06:38,567
So they really let that
witch out of prison!

101
00:06:40,867 --> 00:06:42,267
Amanda!

102
00:06:42,333 --> 00:06:43,667
- Hey! Amanda!
- Rina!

103
00:06:43,733 --> 00:06:45,400
What are you doing?

104
00:06:45,467 --> 00:06:46,833
Now is not the time, Rina!

105
00:06:46,900 --> 00:06:47,867
Why?

106
00:06:47,933 --> 00:06:49,267
Is there a right time to
confront the woman who

107
00:06:49,333 --> 00:06:51,233
killed our son?

108
00:06:51,300 --> 00:06:53,367
Rina! We came here for Red.

109
00:06:53,433 --> 00:06:54,367
Learn to choose
your battles!

110
00:06:54,433 --> 00:06:55,833
That's why I choose this!

111
00:06:55,900 --> 00:07:01,000
I will fight for Angelo's
life as long as I live!

112
00:07:01,067 --> 00:07:03,767
So let go of me because
they are getting away!

113
00:07:03,833 --> 00:07:04,667
- Rina!
- Let go of me!

114
00:07:04,733 --> 00:07:06,967
Amanda!

115
00:07:07,300 --> 00:07:08,000
- Rina!
- Let go!

116
00:07:08,067 --> 00:07:09,033
Amanda!

117
00:07:09,100 --> 00:07:10,233
Amanda!

118
00:07:10,900 --> 00:07:12,467
Amanda! Hey!

119
00:07:12,533 --> 00:07:13,967
Amanda!

120
00:07:22,233 --> 00:07:24,367
You heartless beast!
Monster! Amanda!

121
00:07:24,433 --> 00:07:25,933
- Stop! Rina, stop!
- Let go of me!

122
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:27,567
Amanda!

123
00:07:28,867 --> 00:07:30,267
You beast!

124
00:07:32,233 --> 00:07:34,267
Will you let go of me?

125
00:07:41,733 --> 00:07:44,333
That's Ma'am Rina
and Sir Victor.

126
00:07:44,400 --> 00:07:45,267
What?

127
00:07:45,333 --> 00:07:47,067
Your old employer?

128
00:07:47,133 --> 00:07:48,967
I think so.

129
00:07:49,067 --> 00:07:51,367
What are they doing here?

130
00:07:51,433 --> 00:07:53,833
Perhaps they heard that they
released you from prison.

131
00:07:53,900 --> 00:07:56,067
That's why they're
following you.

132
00:07:56,133 --> 00:08:00,167
Gosh, they seem to be
losing their minds!

133
00:08:00,233 --> 00:08:02,067
Maybe they
haven't moved on.

134
00:08:02,133 --> 00:08:06,267
They're probably still blaming
you for what happened.

135
00:08:06,333 --> 00:08:09,200
If we're not in this
situation, I will face them.

136
00:08:09,267 --> 00:08:11,900
I will let them see
that I'm innocent.

137
00:08:11,967 --> 00:08:15,467
And I proved my innocence
when I got acquitted.

138
00:08:15,533 --> 00:08:17,433
But I have to think of Eden.

139
00:08:17,500 --> 00:08:20,167
I can't waste my time on them.

140
00:08:21,333 --> 00:08:24,033
All I care about is
finding my daughter.

141
00:09:01,133 --> 00:09:02,400
What are you doing?

142
00:09:03,267 --> 00:09:05,200
I'm going to make a raft.

143
00:09:05,267 --> 00:09:06,100
What?

144
00:09:07,433 --> 00:09:09,600
Raft.

145
00:09:09,667 --> 00:09:12,233
We can use this to get
out of this island.

146
00:09:12,300 --> 00:09:14,867
I saw a lot of wood out here.

147
00:09:14,933 --> 00:09:16,700
Didn't you say you have a plan?

148
00:09:17,733 --> 00:09:18,867
What's your plan?

149
00:09:20,100 --> 00:09:20,967
Nothing.

150
00:09:21,033 --> 00:09:22,967
I was planning to
make a fire again.

151
00:09:23,033 --> 00:09:26,400
To signal the rescuers
that we're here.

152
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:28,900
Red.

153
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:32,233
We've been on this
island for days now.

154
00:09:32,300 --> 00:09:33,400
If they had sent out rescuers,

155
00:09:33,467 --> 00:09:35,267
they would have been
here by now.

156
00:09:36,867 --> 00:09:39,100
Let's do something
to get out of here.

157
00:09:40,767 --> 00:09:45,533
And you promised me that we'd
get out of this island.

158
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:48,567
You said we'd be with
our parents again.

159
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:51,767
So please, help me with this.

160
00:09:52,967 --> 00:09:53,500
Okay.

161
00:09:53,567 --> 00:09:54,800
Let's do this.

162
00:09:54,867 --> 00:09:56,167
Okay, good.

163
00:09:56,233 --> 00:09:58,633
Take care of this raft.

164
00:09:58,700 --> 00:10:01,933
I need more wood, so I'm
going back to the forest.

165
00:10:02,033 --> 00:10:03,700
I'll come with you.

166
00:10:03,767 --> 00:10:04,800
Let's go.

167
00:10:05,533 --> 00:10:07,333
I saw a lot of woods that way.

168
00:10:07,400 --> 00:10:08,967
Which way is it?

169
00:10:09,033 --> 00:10:10,067
Over there.

170
00:10:22,067 --> 00:10:23,400
Hon,

171
00:10:23,467 --> 00:10:25,133
breakfast is ready.

172
00:10:36,967 --> 00:10:38,833
Are you still mad at me?

173
00:10:38,900 --> 00:10:44,267
I would have confronted
Amanda if you didn't stop me!

174
00:10:44,333 --> 00:10:47,533
I could have done
something to her!

175
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:49,733
That's the reason why
I stopped you.

176
00:10:49,800 --> 00:10:54,600
I'm scared of what you can do
to her because of your anger.

177
00:10:54,667 --> 00:10:58,333
Look, Hon, at this point,
I wouldn't put it past you

178
00:10:58,400 --> 00:11:02,000
that you would hurt her
badly to get revenge.

179
00:11:02,067 --> 00:11:03,500
And then what?

180
00:11:03,567 --> 00:11:04,967
You will be a criminal?

181
00:11:05,033 --> 00:11:06,700
Is that the kind
of justice you want?

182
00:11:20,200 --> 00:11:22,533
Hon, let's try
to think about this.

183
00:11:23,967 --> 00:11:26,367
Don't let our
anger take control.

184
00:11:27,300 --> 00:11:30,933
Hasn't it crossed your mind?

185
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:35,633
The reason Red is missing
is for you to clear your mind.

186
00:11:35,700 --> 00:11:37,933
And to get your mind
focused on Red alone?

187
00:11:46,067 --> 00:11:48,233
So what are you
trying to say, huh?

188
00:11:48,300 --> 00:11:50,667
That it's my fault
that Red is missing?

189
00:11:50,733 --> 00:11:51,700
What? No!

190
00:11:51,767 --> 00:11:53,367
What? That I'm getting
punished because I'm not

191
00:11:53,433 --> 00:11:54,600
a good enough mother?

192
00:11:54,667 --> 00:11:55,633
Is that it?

193
00:11:55,700 --> 00:11:58,333
Amanda deserves to be punished!

194
00:11:58,400 --> 00:12:00,800
Because she ruined our life!

195
00:12:01,833 --> 00:12:04,000
She killed our firstborn child!

196
00:12:05,067 --> 00:12:07,733
It's all Amanda's fault!

197
00:12:08,933 --> 00:12:10,700
She ruined our family.

198
00:12:11,833 --> 00:12:13,733
She ruined our life!

199
00:12:14,733 --> 00:12:19,567
And I will never
ever forgive her!

200
00:12:35,233 --> 00:12:36,633
You look tired.

201
00:12:36,700 --> 00:12:38,400
Why don't you
get some rest?

202
00:12:38,467 --> 00:12:40,167
No, I'm fine.

203
00:12:40,233 --> 00:12:43,233
We'll get this done faster
if we help each other.

204
00:12:45,167 --> 00:12:46,100
Ouch!

205
00:12:48,267 --> 00:12:49,200
Are you okay?

206
00:12:54,100 --> 00:12:55,067
I'm fine.

207
00:12:57,400 --> 00:12:58,733
You're not being careful.

208
00:12:58,800 --> 00:13:00,933
You're rushing it.

209
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:02,700
I'm trying to get this done.

210
00:13:02,767 --> 00:13:04,900
I want to get out
of this island.

211
00:13:04,967 --> 00:13:07,000
I don't want to stay
here another night.

212
00:13:08,333 --> 00:13:10,067
I'm just worried
about you, Yen.

213
00:13:17,633 --> 00:13:19,633
We need more strings
to tie this up.

214
00:13:19,700 --> 00:13:21,767
I'm going to
gather more vines.

215
00:13:24,233 --> 00:13:25,233
Hey.

216
00:13:26,200 --> 00:13:27,700
See what I mean?

217
00:13:27,767 --> 00:13:29,133
Come on, let's go
to our shelter.

218
00:13:31,300 --> 00:13:32,467
Are you okay?

219
00:13:40,433 --> 00:13:41,400
You must be dehydrated.

220
00:13:41,467 --> 00:13:42,233
That's why you got dizzy.

221
00:13:42,300 --> 00:13:43,267
Drink some water.

222
00:13:49,933 --> 00:13:51,600
That's good.

223
00:13:51,667 --> 00:13:52,733
I'm fine now.

224
00:13:53,500 --> 00:13:55,433
I want to get
the raft done.

225
00:13:55,533 --> 00:13:56,333
Yen!
Stay here for now.

226
00:13:57,400 --> 00:13:59,033
Come sit down for now.

227
00:13:59,100 --> 00:14:00,367
Come on.

228
00:14:00,433 --> 00:14:02,033
I'll get the raft done.

229
00:14:02,100 --> 00:14:04,633
I'll get it done
fast, I promise!

230
00:14:04,700 --> 00:14:06,933
You must be getting
annoyed with me.

231
00:14:10,633 --> 00:14:11,600
Yen,

232
00:14:11,667 --> 00:14:13,500
I understand.

233
00:14:13,567 --> 00:14:16,867
I know that you want
to get out of this island.

234
00:14:16,933 --> 00:14:22,400
But it won't happen if one of us
gets injured or harmed.

235
00:14:22,467 --> 00:14:24,233
So it's better if you stay
here and get your strength back.

236
00:14:24,300 --> 00:14:25,233
Get some rest.

237
00:14:25,300 --> 00:14:26,400
I'll get the raft done.

238
00:14:26,467 --> 00:14:28,300
Okay? I got it.

239
00:15:03,133 --> 00:15:07,800
You said you'd call me
to give an update

240
00:15:07,867 --> 00:15:09,033
about the investigation.

241
00:15:09,100 --> 00:15:11,633
You haven't contacted me.

242
00:15:11,700 --> 00:15:12,333
I'm sorry, Ma'am.

243
00:15:12,400 --> 00:15:14,767
But we still have no news.

244
00:15:14,833 --> 00:15:17,133
They still can't pinpoint
the exact location

245
00:15:17,200 --> 00:15:18,700
where the plane crashed.

246
00:15:18,767 --> 00:15:21,333
So it's hard to do
search and rescue.

247
00:15:21,400 --> 00:15:22,300
I've already heard that.

248
00:15:22,367 --> 00:15:24,433
That's what you said before.

249
00:15:24,500 --> 00:15:29,467
You should do your job better!

250
00:15:29,533 --> 00:15:31,200
So you can find my daughter!

251
00:15:31,267 --> 00:15:33,233
You have to find Eden!

252
00:15:33,300 --> 00:15:39,133
Actually, I've been instructed
to tell the passengers' families

253
00:15:39,233 --> 00:15:40,767
that the longer
the search takes,

254
00:15:40,833 --> 00:15:44,533
the smaller chance
that they'll be found alive.

255
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:46,533
What did you say?

256
00:15:46,600 --> 00:15:48,967
I'm sorry, Ma'am, but we only
want to prepare you

257
00:15:49,033 --> 00:15:50,967
for what can happen.

258
00:16:18,400 --> 00:16:19,467
Water?

259
00:16:21,200 --> 00:16:22,600
Thank you.

260
00:16:22,667 --> 00:16:24,667
I should be thanking you.

261
00:16:24,733 --> 00:16:26,700
I got some rest
because of you.

262
00:16:26,767 --> 00:16:27,933
Let me help you.

263
00:16:29,367 --> 00:16:30,767
Let me see this.

264
00:16:33,900 --> 00:16:35,867
I'm sorry I didn't
get a lot done.

265
00:16:37,467 --> 00:16:40,267
I tied the wood together.

266
00:16:40,333 --> 00:16:43,633
We'll be riding this, so we
should make it sturdy, right?

267
00:16:48,833 --> 00:16:50,100
Are you disappointed?

268
00:16:52,667 --> 00:16:54,067
You're doing it right.

269
00:16:54,133 --> 00:16:55,133
It's just that...

270
00:16:55,200 --> 00:16:56,367
What?

271
00:16:56,433 --> 00:16:59,633
I just want to get
out of this island.

272
00:16:59,700 --> 00:17:00,667
Right now!

273
00:17:01,533 --> 00:17:04,333
I want to forget this nightmare!

274
00:17:06,600 --> 00:17:08,033
Red,

275
00:17:08,100 --> 00:17:09,800
I want to get out of here.

276
00:17:12,267 --> 00:17:15,600
I want to forget everything
that's happening here.

277
00:17:16,533 --> 00:17:19,533
Let's get this done!

278
00:17:48,467 --> 00:17:49,533
No!

279
00:17:51,367 --> 00:17:53,833
That's impossible to happen!

280
00:17:53,900 --> 00:17:56,167
Do you know my daughter?

281
00:17:56,233 --> 00:17:57,767
You don't know her!

282
00:17:58,767 --> 00:18:00,500
She's courageous,

283
00:18:00,567 --> 00:18:02,133
she's strong.

284
00:18:03,467 --> 00:18:05,933
Eden is a survivor.

285
00:18:07,967 --> 00:18:10,100
My daughter's been
through a lot.

286
00:18:10,900 --> 00:18:13,667
She's been through
a lot because of me.

287
00:18:13,733 --> 00:18:17,967
But she never gave
up, not even once!

288
00:18:18,033 --> 00:18:22,300
She endured everything
without me.

289
00:18:22,400 --> 00:18:24,600
So what you're
saying is impossible!

290
00:18:24,667 --> 00:18:27,100
My daughter still has dreams!

291
00:18:27,167 --> 00:18:30,000
She still has a long way to go.

292
00:18:35,467 --> 00:18:39,600
She's not going to die.

293
00:18:40,733 --> 00:18:42,800
My daughter's not going to die.

294
00:18:45,500 --> 00:18:46,667
Amanda?

295
00:18:46,733 --> 00:18:48,133
Amanda, what's going on?

296
00:18:48,200 --> 00:18:50,000
Who are you talking to?

297
00:18:50,067 --> 00:18:51,433
My god.

298
00:18:59,333 --> 00:19:00,667
Amanda, what's wrong?

299
00:19:03,100 --> 00:19:06,033
I don't want my daughter to die.

300
00:19:06,100 --> 00:19:10,600
My god, my daughter can't die.

301
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:45,767
Everything you said earlier

302
00:19:45,833 --> 00:19:47,067
will happen.

303
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:51,267
We're doing something
about it, right?

304
00:19:53,233 --> 00:19:55,600
We'll get this raft done.

305
00:19:56,900 --> 00:20:00,100
Even if we don't get
this done by tonight.

306
00:20:00,167 --> 00:20:01,200
We'll go tomorrow.

307
00:20:05,133 --> 00:20:06,567
We'll get this done.

308
00:20:26,167 --> 00:20:28,400
We also need to
make paddles.

309
00:20:28,467 --> 00:20:30,800
We need to make paddles
to get this thing going.

310
00:20:33,467 --> 00:20:35,433
Actually, I'm excited.

311
00:20:35,533 --> 00:20:39,467
If we get this to work,
we'll be out for an adventure.

312
00:20:39,533 --> 00:20:40,933
It's like sailing.

313
00:20:43,400 --> 00:20:45,100
I envy you.

314
00:20:45,167 --> 00:20:50,367
You can stay positive
after all this.

315
00:20:50,433 --> 00:20:51,900
Of course.

316
00:20:51,967 --> 00:20:59,267
As athletes, we have to keep
a positive mindset, right?

317
00:20:59,333 --> 00:21:03,933
It will keep us going
if we have a positive mindset.

318
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:06,467
We can envision our goals more.

319
00:21:06,533 --> 00:21:07,733
That's it.

320
00:21:08,900 --> 00:21:10,733
What about you?

321
00:21:10,800 --> 00:21:14,900
Once we get this raft done
and get to sail out...

322
00:21:14,967 --> 00:21:17,667
what do you think
we'll see first?

323
00:21:21,200 --> 00:21:25,467
I think we'll find a place
with lots of people.

324
00:21:25,533 --> 00:21:27,800
They will help us out.

325
00:21:27,867 --> 00:21:34,200
And they will feed us
delicious seafood.

326
00:21:34,267 --> 00:21:36,000
And more importantly, we'll have
a good reception there,

327
00:21:36,067 --> 00:21:38,167
and we can contact our parents.

328
00:21:39,900 --> 00:21:42,600
What about you? What do you
think we'll see first?

329
00:21:45,933 --> 00:21:47,133
A ship!

330
00:21:47,600 --> 00:21:48,767
A ship.

331
00:21:48,833 --> 00:21:51,500
I hope it's a cruise ship
so we'll have a lot of food.

332
00:21:51,567 --> 00:21:54,767
Red, I'm not just
dreaming about the ship!

333
00:21:54,833 --> 00:21:56,500
There's a ship!

334
00:21:59,200 --> 00:22:00,767
Help!

335
00:22:00,833 --> 00:22:01,467
Help!

336
00:22:01,533 --> 00:22:03,600
Yen! Wait!

337
00:22:03,667 --> 00:22:04,333
Yen!

338
00:22:05,167 --> 00:22:06,433
- Help!
- Yen, wait!

339
00:22:10,867 --> 00:22:12,133
- Help!
- Wait!

340
00:22:12,200 --> 00:22:13,700
- Help!
- We're here!

341
00:22:13,767 --> 00:22:14,900
Help!

342
00:22:16,900 --> 00:22:18,667
- Help!
- We're here!

343
00:22:20,633 --> 00:22:22,000
Help!

344
00:22:23,100 --> 00:22:24,667
We're here!

345
00:22:24,733 --> 00:22:26,633
- Help! We're here!
- Help!

346
00:22:26,700 --> 00:22:27,400
Yen!

347
00:22:27,467 --> 00:22:29,267
They won't hear us from here.

348
00:22:29,333 --> 00:22:31,267
Let's go closer, then!

349
00:22:31,333 --> 00:22:32,100
How?
Let's swim there!

350
00:22:33,133 --> 00:22:33,500
Let's go!

351
00:22:33,567 --> 00:22:35,700
What? Wait!

352
00:22:35,767 --> 00:22:37,900
Do you realize what
you want to do?

353
00:22:37,967 --> 00:22:39,067
What?

354
00:22:39,133 --> 00:22:41,800
Yen! The ferry's way too far!

355
00:22:41,867 --> 00:22:43,467
How are you going
to swim there?

356
00:22:43,533 --> 00:22:45,033
Can we pull it off?

357
00:22:45,100 --> 00:22:47,267
We'll never know
unless we try!

358
00:22:47,333 --> 00:22:48,833
- Let's go!
- Wait.

359
00:22:48,933 --> 00:22:50,067
Yen,

360
00:22:50,133 --> 00:22:51,600
you have to think about this.

361
00:22:51,667 --> 00:22:52,367
Okay?

362
00:22:52,433 --> 00:22:54,200
I've been thinking for so long.

363
00:22:54,267 --> 00:22:56,200
When we landed
on this island,

364
00:22:56,267 --> 00:22:58,667
I had already been thinking
of a way to get out of here!

365
00:22:58,733 --> 00:23:00,633
Now, we have the
opportunity!

366
00:23:00,700 --> 00:23:02,000
Let's go!

367
00:23:02,067 --> 00:23:02,833
Yen, wait.
I can't let this
opportunity pass.

368
00:23:03,833 --> 00:23:04,433
Let's go.

369
00:23:05,467 --> 00:23:06,733
Yen!

370
00:23:06,800 --> 00:23:08,300
I won't force you to do
this if you don't want to!

371
00:23:08,367 --> 00:23:10,400
Only one person has
to swim out there.

372
00:23:10,467 --> 00:23:12,933
I'll ask the
rescuers to get you.

373
00:23:13,000 --> 00:23:14,167
Wait, wait!

374
00:23:14,233 --> 00:23:15,933
What are you doing?

375
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:16,933
Yen.

376
00:23:18,833 --> 00:23:20,033
Okay.

377
00:23:20,100 --> 00:23:22,967
If this is what you want,
we're gonna do this together.

378
00:23:23,067 --> 00:23:24,033
No one will get
left behind.

379
00:23:24,100 --> 00:23:24,800
Okay?

380
00:23:26,433 --> 00:23:28,433
Here's the plan.

381
00:23:28,500 --> 00:23:32,133
We're going to swim to them
so they can see us.

382
00:23:32,200 --> 00:23:35,167
And then you'll blow the whistle
to get their attention.

383
00:23:35,233 --> 00:23:36,400
- Okay.
- Okay?

384
00:23:37,167 --> 00:23:38,867
Stay with me.

385
00:23:38,933 --> 00:23:40,133
Don't let go.

386
00:23:49,233 --> 00:23:54,700
Let's go.

387
00:23:58,133 --> 00:24:00,000
Lord,

388
00:24:00,067 --> 00:24:02,567
I trust in you.

389
00:24:02,633 --> 00:24:04,867
I know that you'll take
care of my daughter.

390
00:24:07,967 --> 00:24:11,600
Wherever she is,

391
00:24:11,667 --> 00:24:15,067
please keep her safe.

392
00:24:19,367 --> 00:24:22,433
Red, we have to make noise
so they can hear us.

393
00:24:22,500 --> 00:24:23,067
Okay.

394
00:24:23,133 --> 00:24:24,300
- Help!
- Help!

395
00:24:24,367 --> 00:24:25,533
Help!

396
00:24:25,600 --> 00:24:28,967
Please keep my
daughter safe.

397
00:24:29,067 --> 00:24:32,767
Please give
her back to me.

398
00:24:32,833 --> 00:24:35,200
Please give her
back to me alive.

399
00:24:37,600 --> 00:24:38,467
Help!

400
00:24:38,533 --> 00:24:39,667
Help!

401
00:24:41,433 --> 00:24:42,400
Keep on whistling!

402
00:24:42,467 --> 00:24:43,233
Keep blowing the whistle!

403
00:24:44,000 --> 00:24:46,100
- Help!
- Help!

404
00:24:46,167 --> 00:24:48,267
Red, we have to get closer!

405
00:24:48,333 --> 00:24:49,600
Let's go.

406
00:24:49,667 --> 00:24:51,633
We'll be safe now!

407
00:24:53,667 --> 00:24:55,967
- We're going to be saved!
- We're here!

408
00:25:01,867 --> 00:25:06,267
They've already found survivors
on an island near Davao.

409
00:25:06,333 --> 00:25:07,767
They're checking who
survivors' identities.

410
00:25:07,833 --> 00:25:10,067
They said there's a woman
as same as Yenyen's age.

411
00:25:10,133 --> 00:25:11,300
Why the long face?

412
00:25:11,367 --> 00:25:13,500
You know, you should be happy!

413
00:25:13,567 --> 00:25:15,400
I have a very strong feeling

414
00:25:15,467 --> 00:25:19,400
that Red is one
of the rescued survivors.

415
00:25:19,467 --> 00:25:21,733
I just don't want us
to feel disappointed.

416
00:25:21,800 --> 00:25:22,933
Especially you, Rina.

417
00:25:23,000 --> 00:25:25,733
The recovered survivors
are still unconscious right now.

418
00:25:25,800 --> 00:25:28,567
But requested videos
from the hospital

419
00:25:28,633 --> 00:25:32,167
so you can check if your
relatives are one of them.

420
00:25:32,233 --> 00:25:34,400
Are you following
me even here?

421
00:25:34,467 --> 00:25:36,800
Why would we
follow you around?

422
00:25:36,900 --> 00:25:39,333
I'm here to find
my daughter.

423
00:25:39,400 --> 00:25:42,433
While you popped out of
nowhere to cause trouble.

424
00:25:42,500 --> 00:25:45,400
Is she one of the passengers
of the plane that crashed?

425
00:25:45,467 --> 00:25:48,467
Do you know someone
from that flight too?

426
00:25:48,533 --> 00:25:49,800
Who is it?
